cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.PL 

This paper is likely to belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as it deals with the problem of obtaining relational structures of the environment in Reinforcement Learning, which is a subfield of AI. It also proposes an unsupervised architecture for grounding first-order logic predicates and facts, which is a common problem in AI. 

It is also likely to belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it uses a neural network called State AutoEncoder (SAE) to encode an image-based input into a propositional representation compatible with classical planning. 

cs.CV (Computer Vision) is another likely sub-category as the paper deals with obtaining relational structures from images. 

cs.RO (Robotics) is also a possible sub-category as the paper deals with obtaining a compact, abstract model of the environment, which is a common problem in robotics. 

Finally, cs.PL (Programming Languages) is a possible sub-category as the paper proposes a model that is compatible with symbolic classical planning, which is a common problem in programming languages.
